=== 使用情況 ===

==== 行政 ====
印度中央政府在行政事務上只使用英語和印地語。但印度憲法規定，公民有權使用任何一種印度境內的語言（不論其官方語言地位）上書冤情。對於各邦及聯邦屬地的官方語言，則由地方政府定奪，但若邦內的其他重要族群亦想自己族群的語言在邦內官方化，則有權上書印度總理，後者在考量後有權要求地方政府補充官方語言。

另外，不論官方地位如何，各邦政府皆有義務爲所有少數族群提供母語基礎教育。

==== 議會 ====
印度議會的發言語言需要爲英語或印地語，但對於兩種官方語言都無法使用的議員，若經議會長同意，亦有權使用其母語在議會中發言。

印度憲法規定，除非議會另作決定，否則議會通過的所有法律必須使用英語。目前印度議會亦尚未另作決定，只是規定所有法律需同時翻譯爲印地語，但依然以英文版本爲準。

==== 法院 ====
印度最高法院規定聯邦最高法院及各地方最高法院必須使用英語。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/court-language-is-english-says-supreme-court/articleshow/50080870.cms|title=Court language is English, says Supreme Court – The Economic Times|work=The Economic Times|access-date=30 May 2017|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111215120/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/court-language-is-english-says-supreme-court/articleshow/50080870.cms|dead-url=no}}</ref> 但四個屬邦<ref>[http://www.barandbench.com/index.php?title=Language%20in%20Courts%20-%20a%20bridge%20or%20a%20barrier?&page=brief&id=805&gn=0 Language in Courts – a bridge or a barrier?]{{dead link|date=August 2020}}</ref>——[[比哈尔邦|比哈尔邦]]、[[中央邦|中央邦]]、[[拉贾斯坦邦|拉贾斯坦邦]]、[[北方邦|北方邦]]——有權在其最高法院中使用印地語。[[泰米尔纳德邦|泰米尔纳德邦]]亦曾要求被賦予在其轄區法院使用泰米爾語的權力，但被印度最高法院拒絕<ref>{{citation|last=Special Correspondent|title=Karunanidhi stands firm on Tamil in High Court|newspaper=The Hindu|page=1|date=12 March 2007|url=http://www.hindu.com/2007/03/12/stories/2007031205180100.htm|accessdate=2020-09-03|archive-date=2007-03-13|archive-url=https://archive.today/20070313221430/http://www.hindu.com/2007/03/12/stories/2007031205180100.htm|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。2006年，印度政府稱不會再反對[[泰米尔纳德邦|泰米尔纳德邦]]的請求<ref>[http://www.hindu.com/2006/12/03/stories/2006120306220800.htm The Hindu: Tamil Nadu / Thanjavur News: No objection to Tamil as court language: A.P. Shah<!-- Bot-generated title -->] {{Wayback|url=http://www.hindu.com/2006/12/03/stories/2006120306220800.htm |date=20070107191048 }} 2006/12/03 ''www.hindu.com'', accessed 4 August 2020</ref>，2010年開始，[[泰米尔纳德邦|泰米尔纳德邦]]允許使用泰米爾語作爲法庭抗辯語言<ref>{{cite news|title=Advocate argues in Tamil in High Court|url=http://newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/article443474.ece|accessdate=27 June 2010|newspaper=[[The_New_Indian_Express|The New Indian Express]]|date=23 June 2010|archive-date=2016-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160315132338/http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/article443474.ece|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==== 聯邦及各邦屬的通信 ====
聯邦政府與各邦屬之間的通信用語分爲三種情況：

# A區域的邦屬政府及公民，即本身地方官方語言就爲印地語（或之一），與聯邦政府使用印地語通信<ref>{{cite web|title=The Official Languages (Use for Official Purpose of the Union) – Rules 1976 (As Amended, 1987) – Paragraph 3(1)|url=http://www.rajbhasha.gov.in/dolruleseng.htm|accessdate=10 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100325173337/http://www.rajbhasha.gov.in/dolruleseng.htm|archive-date=2010-03-25|dead-url=no}}</ref>；
# B區域的邦屬政府，即本身地方官方語言並非印地語，但卻依然使用印地語與聯邦政府通信，該類邦屬有[[马哈拉施特拉邦|馬哈拉施特拉邦]]及[[旁遮普邦|旁遮普邦]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Official Languages (Use for Official Purpose of the Union) – Rules 1976 (As Amended, 1987) – Paragraph 2(g)|url=http://www.rajbhasha.gov.in/dolruleseng.htm|accessdate=10 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100325173337/http://www.rajbhasha.gov.in/dolruleseng.htm|archive-date=2010-03-25|dead-url=no}}</ref>；而聯邦政府與B區域邦屬公民的通信語言則爲英語及印地語；
# C區域的邦屬政府與公民，即本身地方官方語言並非印地語，與聯邦政府的通信語言爲英語<ref>{{cite web|title=The Official Languages (Use for Official Purpose of the Union) – Rules 1976 (As Amended, 1987) – Paragraph 3(3)|url=http://www.rajbhasha.gov.in/dolruleseng.htm|accessdate=10 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100325173337/http://www.rajbhasha.gov.in/dolruleseng.htm|archive-date=2010-03-25|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==== 推廣 ====
印度政府在[[泰米尔纳德邦|泰米尔纳德邦]]首府[[金奈|金奈]]設立了{{Link-en|Dakshina Bharat Hindustani Prachar Sabha）||南印度印地語普及協會}}，負責[[印度南部|印南各邦]]的印地語推廣事宜。2016年，印度政府宣佈將採取措施在印度南部及東北部推廣印地語。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Centre to promote the use of Hindi in South India, Northeast:<br/>In response to this several NGO and political parties have started agitation and some have even resorted to violent protests in the Darjeeling for separate statehood, which started in after the official statement in a press meet by Central parliamentary affairs minister. The monster himself hails from South India and many party leader of the government has felt like an insult to the mother language. The TANA has stated "It's high time the North should learn the lessons from the past and should try not to stir the broth"<br/>The ADMK leader has said in New Delhi "It's a shame to see my neighboring state leader hailing from Telugu state speaking against his own mother tongue.<br/>The Dravida Samrakshana Samiti Head has said " it's a direct assault on our culture and is an insult for saying the minister hailing from South India. (Jitendra Singh)|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/centre-to-promote-use-of-hindi-in-south-india-northeast-jitendra-singh/|date=9 June 2016|website=The Indian Express|access-date=11 June 2016|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108090506/https://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/centre-to-promote-use-of-hindi-in-south-india-northeast-jitendra-singh/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

